<br>
'yes, there was a vox raid earlier.'<br>
<br>
'and an item dropp.  the item that was dropped was a rbb.  The raid leader left with the item before the raid could roll on it'<br>
<br>
'loreleis my friend rolled a 997 on the item when it was determined that the raid leader would not come back.  His name was'<br>
<br>
'maleras.  Everytime he logged on he would immediatly log off, and the raid did not hear a word from him.'<br>
<br>
'I'm really fraustrated he would do this, I heard the white dragon'<br>
<br>
'which he also left with at the time was given to the winner of the /random.  However I could not confirm'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'Alright, unfortunatly, since it was the raid leader who took it there may not be much that can be done about it.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'if the raid leader was in the group that landed the kill strike, there is not anything we can do.  Were any /reports done of the killing blow?'<br>
<br>
'Not that I know of.  I could not confirm that.'<br>
<br>
'All i know is that there was a raid.  The loot rules were set.  The rules stated all could roll on the belt.  And the raid leader left without letting people roll.  Those were the rules he set.  Instead, he gated out and immediatly went LD'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'There really wouldn't be enough evidence if no /reporst were made of the killing blow.  I'm sorry but there is not much we can do without them.'<br>
<br>
<br>
'I did make a report, but I was not in the zone when she died.  For all I know I could of landed the killing blow; I was booted out using Denons desperate dirge as she had less then 500 hp.  I did report it but not the killing blow.'<br>
<br>
'and does it seem logical to report the killing blow?  or practical for that manner.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells  you, 'Then there is not much that we can do.  We have no proof of what group actually killed the monster.  Without that, we have no evidence that it was in fact ninja looted.'<br>
<br>
'I believe rhaje has that specific evidence; he is not online right now.  He both logged the fight as well as made screen shots.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you 'we cannot use the screen shots as evidence, as users can alter them.  We can only use /reports. Without those, we cannot do anything.  I'm sorry.'<br>
<br>
' Is there any other GM I can speak with concerning this manner.  I've been told Gms have the ability to go through logs and verify that evidence without the need of /report.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'We do not log everything that is said in this game.  We do not log who kills what monster.  Again, without the /reports, we have no evidence to support your claims.  I am sorry, but there is nothing we can do without those.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'Safe hunting, and good night.'<br>
<br>
'So basically you're telling me if you make a raid, and the raid leader makes the killing blow and he loots everything.   There is nothing you can do about it.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'If the people in the group that make the killing blow on a mob(and have done enough damage to gain the experience) then they may do what they choose to with the loot.'<br>
<br>
<br>
'but you see, specifically the group has that choose.  The &quot;group&quot;  as you said &quot;they&quot; they decided the item should be rolled upon.  Everyone decided it was to be rolled upon.  The item was not rolled upon.  An individual took the item.'<br>
<br>
'and made the Soul decision that the item would be his, without letting &quot;they&quot; roll on it.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, 'I will still need /reports from that group of making the killing blow, and also of their agreement that all people there should roll upon the items.'<br>
<br>
<br>
'there was specifically that agreement.  Even the raid leader made that agreement.  If that is the fact, then how does who kills what matter at all?'<br>
<br>
'if it were to be any group and any scenario it still would be the same.  Even if his did or did not get the killing blow he would of left.'<br>
<br>
pardima tells you, 'again, we need /reports proving that that was the agreement.  and teh rule of the people who kill a mob determine what happens to that loot stands for all mobs in the game, in all situations.'<br>
<br>
'with the item and with out the consent of the people who raided with him.  Whom he made that agreement with.'<br>
<br>
'did you bother looking through the reports?   I did make a report, it said the last 10 lines would be reported.  That's it.  Should I make it standard procedure to /report everything on the raid.'<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you,' I don't show any reports related to any sort of looting, or vox.  I'm sorry.'<br>
<br>
'did you look through just mine?  or everyones?<br>
<br>
Pardima tells you, ' I looked through the entire server's reports.'<br>
<br>
'Ok.  Well thank you for your time.  I will tell everyone on the nameless it is now required to /report everything on every pick up raid for you guys to assist in ninja looting.  Good night.'<br>
<br>
Question, Does this seem rediculous to you?  Because it sure as hell does to me.<br>
